com.facebook.model
Interface OpenGraphObject

All Superinterfaces:
GraphObject
public interface OpenGraphObject
extends GraphObject

Provides a strongly-typed representation of an Open Graph Object. For more documentation of OG Objects, see: https://developers.facebook.com/docs/opengraph/using-object-api/ Note that this interface is intended to be used with GraphObject.Factory or OpenGraphObject.Factory and not implemented directly.

getCreateObject

boolean getCreateObject()
Gets whether the object represents a new object that should be created as part of publishing via, e.g., the native Share dialog. This flag has no effect on explicit publishing of an action via, e.g., a POST to the '/me/objects/object_type' endpoint.

Returns:
true if the native Share dialog should create the object as part of publishing an action, false if not

setCreateObject

void setCreateObject(boolean createObject)
Sets whether the object represents a new object that should be created as part of publishing via, e.g., the native Share dialog. This flag has no effect on explicit publishing of an action via, e.g., a POST to the '/me/objects/object_type' endpoint.

Parameters:
createObject - true if the native Share dialog should create the object as part of publishing an action, false if not
